**[1846, 03-23] Ms.A.1.2.16.24**

Mott to RDW; Philadelphia

The Webbs’ change of sect from the Friends; peace question; Ballou and
non-resistance, Theodore Parker’s writings. “Sarah Pugh brought your
last after Abby Kimber had had it, for us to enjoy puzzling it out
together. She always allows me to look over her shoulder while reading,
and ‘best fellow’ finds out the hard words first. James Mott sitting by,
profiting by our united facility of deciphering illegible characters,
and really enjoying every word as much as we do. After we had finished
it, she agreed to have it with me a few days, as an aid in writing again
to you.” Praises Wright’s interesting letters from abroad.


